review_blob: 12 Oz can with rip off lid poured into a flute. Nice lasting head with lacing, bread, cereal, dough aromas lightly malted and hopped, very delicious great for a session. If you ever want to blow away a crotchety macro brew lover hand em this

12 Oz bottle poured into a tulip golden color with a small quickly dissipating head with no lacing, slighty funky sweet smelling aroma, flavor was kind of tart nicely carbonated but kind of wine cooler like. I expected way better from dogfish head the maker of one of my favorite beers 90 min ipa
12 Oz bottle poured into a tulip, 1 finger lasting head with nice lacing, fruity malty aroma and tastes the same. More malty than hoppy but I prefer the latter not bad though
11.2 Oz bottle poured into a tulip, humongous long lasting head with lacing. fruity aroma. Pear, bubblegum, tropical fruit flavors. Delicious tasting beer that is easily available

12 Oz bottle poured into a pint glass, amber color with nice head and lacing, grassy hop aromas. Typical IPA taste not too hoppy not too malty nice balance. Kind of sad A.B. Inbev is linked to this company

12 Oz bottle poured into a flute, nice lasting head with some lacing, bread, hay, citrus, dough, lightly hopped, could drink all day
12 Oz bottle. Golden color with huge lasting head with some lacing, funky aroma, citrus, wheaty taste, very refreshing and quite delicious
12 Oz bottle pitch black with beige head, chocolate, coffee, roasty, toast, nuts, smoke. Cream of the crop if you enjoy Porters

review_blob: 12 Oz bottle poured into a pint glass, orange brown color and decent lasting head, caramel, citrus, vanilla, nicely hopped. Not as good as Sierra Nevada ruthless rye but pretty darn good

review_blob: 12Oz bottle poured into a pint glass yellow cloudy appearance, one finger slowly dissipating head, skunky aroma but very tasty. I would drink this often if it wasnt so salty. Im sure that sea salt will bring your blood pressure up in the long run
Copper amber appearance, toast, citrus, vanilla, nice lasting head with good lacing. Excellent session beer
16Oz can poured into Stein. Nice golden color decent head little lacing, bread, cereal, very metallic. better than any macro swill but not by much

11.2oz bottle poured into hoegaarden hex. Cloudy yellow with a thin head some lacing. Sour sweet taste some citrus some weird spice I can?t put my finger on but very refreshing. If you like witbeirs it is a must try but very expensive $60 for a case sheesh
12Oz bottle into a tulip. copper colored, caramel, citrus, citrus hops. Very nice easy drinker wont even notice that 7.5%
11.2 Oz bottle poured into a pilsner flute, nice head some retention, bread, hay, floral, dough. the gold standard for a pilsener I wish it wasnt so hard to obtain

12Oz bottle poured into pint glass nice One finger head with some lacing, floral, grass, barnyard, earthy taste but it doesnt work well. Its like a mixture of Prima Pils, Helios ale and Whirlwind mixed into one. Not horrible but nothing I would put in my session rotation
